snippet.title: JAZZ at LAKERS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | February 10, 2025
snippet.description:
The Lakers defeated the Jazz, 132-113 tonight in Los Angeles. LeBron James contributed a team-high 24 points to go with 8 assists 7 rebounds and 3 three pointers, with Austin Reaves of the Lakers adding an additional 22 points (6-10 FG, 3-5 3P), 9 rebounds, and 4 assists in the game. Lauri Markkanen finished with a team-high 17 points along with 3 rebounds for the Jazz in the losing effort. The Lakers improve their record to 32-19 with the win, while the Jazz fall to 12-40 for the season. The teams will meet again in their next game on Wednesday, 2/12/2025, when the Jazz host the Lakers (9:00 PM ET, KJZZ/Spectrum SportsNet).

snippet.title: WARRIORS at LAKERS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | February 6, 2025
snippet.description:
The Lakers defeated the Warriors, 120-112 tonight in Los Angeles. LeBron James finished with a season-high 42 points along with 17 rebounds and 8 assists for the Lakers, while Austin Reaves tallied 23 points, 4 assists and 3 rebounds in the game. Stephen Curry recorded 37 points, 7 rebounds and 6 three-pointers. The Lakers improve their record to 30-19 with the win, while the Warriors fall to 25-26 for the season. The Lakers' next game is Saturday, 2/8/2025, against the Pacers on the road (4:00 PM ET, ESPN/ESPN+/Disney+), while the Warriors continue their road trip on Saturday, 2/8/2025, when they face the Bulls (8:00 PM ET, Chicago Sports Network Plus/NBCSBA).

Never miss a moment with the latest news, trending stories and highlights to bring you closer to your favorite players and teams.
